# ===========================================================================
# Secrets. Nothing here ever reaches a remote.
# ===========================================================================
.env
.env.*
*.key
.streamlit/secrets.toml

# ===========================================================================
# Environment and caches
# ===========================================================================
.venv/
venv/
env/
__pycache__/
*.py[cod]
.ipynb_checkpoints/
.DS_Store
Thumbs.db

# ===========================================================================
# Raw data: 8.8 GB. cro_submissions_raw.jsonl alone is 8 GB, and
# Company_Records.csv (183 MB) and cro_submissions_summary.csv (117 MB) are
# each over GitHub's 100 MB hard limit, so they could not be pushed even if
# that were wanted. All of it is public CRO data; the README says where it
# comes from and the notebooks document the collection.
# ===========================================================================
data/raw/

# ===========================================================================
# Processed data. Block the directory, then re-admit the one file the
# dashboard loads. Git cannot re-include a file whose parent directory is
# excluded, which is why this is written as data/* rather than data/.
#
# train_set.csv (86 MB) and test_set.csv (83 MB) stay out: they exist to train
# and evaluate, the model is already trained, and the notebooks rebuild them.
# ===========================================================================
data/*
!data/processed/
data/processed/*
!data/processed/prospective_final.csv

# ===========================================================================
# Derived arrays the dashboard never opens
# ===========================================================================
# 85 MB of sentence embeddings, an input to topic modelling, which is cut.
outputs/nlp/embeddings.npy
# 81 MB narrative corpus. nlp_04's kept output is llm_features.csv.
outputs/nlp/corpus.csv
# Per-company SHAP matrix. The dashboard reads top_drivers_json from
# prospective_shap.csv and computes live SHAP from the model itself.
outputs/prospective_shap_values.npy

# ===========================================================================
# Models. The dashboard loads the winner named in winner_meta.csv plus the
# calibrator. The four also-rans belong to the dissertation's comparison
# table, not to the running app; random_forest_model.joblib alone is 39 MB.
# ===========================================================================
models/random_forest_model.joblib
models/lightgbm_model.joblib
models/decision_tree_model.joblib
models/logistic_regression_model.joblib

# ===========================================================================
# Scratch
# ===========================================================================
app.py
app_1.py
app_hud.py
build_deploy_bundle.py
*.log
*.tmp
~$*
